# =========================================================================
# .env.example — booth & CCA code configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (never committed) for local dev, and add these
# same variables in the Vercel dashboard under Project Settings → Environment
# Variables for production.
#
# The card has two kinds of stamp:
#   - b0  : the mandatory "START HERE" Vivace Gamebooth (models/booths.js)
#   - c1..c86 : the 86 CCA fringe stamps (models/cca-catalog-data.js).
#     The client-side JS picks 11 at random per user, so any CCA_CODE_N
#     could end up being used — set them all.
#
# Only the plaintext codes below are secret. What ships to the browser is
# simpleHash(code) — computed at server boot from these env values.
#
# Codes are randomly generated 6-character strings mixing uppercase letters
# and digits (I/O and 0/1 excluded to avoid mistyping at the booth).
# Regenerate before the event by re-running the generator or by hand —
# no source code changes needed, just redeploy after updating.
# =========================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# START HERE booth
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
BOOTH_CODE_B0=3N4796

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Academic-Based Clubs (BONDUE)
